cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.RO, cs.CG 

The paper deals with 3D shape registration, which is a common problem in computer vision and graphics. The use of landmarks and pose normalization suggests that the paper may belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) or graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. The adaptive shape template method and the iterative registration method are also relevant to machine learning (cs.MM), robotics (cs.RO), and computational geometry (cs.CG). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.GR, followed by cs.MM, cs.RO, and cs.CG.
